{"lemma":"تابُوتٌ","slug":"تابُوتٌ","root":"ت.ب.ت","root_slug":"ت-ب-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ب-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تابُوت","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3774","n4174"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"box, case, chest, coffer, ark","examples":[{"text":"أَنِ ٱقْذِفِيهِ فِي ٱلتَّابُوتِ فَٱقْذِفِيهِ فِي ٱلْيَمِّ فَلْيُلْقِهِ ٱلْيَمُّ بِٱلسَّاحِلِ","english":"Cast him into the chest and cast it into the river, and the river will throw it onto the bank."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coffin, casket, sarcophagus","examples":[{"text":"مَاذَا وَرَاءَ حِكَايَةِ ٱكْتِشَافِ تَابُوتِ ٱلْمَسِيحِ فِي ٱلْقُدْسِ؟","english":"What's behind the story of the discovery of the coffin of Christ in Jerusalem?"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From earlier تَوَبُوت (tawabūt) or تَاوْبُوَّة (tāwbuwwa), from Classical Syriac ܬܝܒܘܬܐ (tēḇūṯā) or Ge'ez ታቦት (tabot). Cognate with Hebrew תיבה (tevá).\nUltimately from a merger of Egyptian DbA-b-t:pr (ḏbꜣt, “sarcophagus, coffin”) and d-b-t:xt (dbt, “chest, box”); compare Demotic Egyptian tbyt (“sarcophagus, shrine, chest”), dbt, and tbt (“chest”) and Coptic ⲧⲁⲓⲃⲉ (taibe, “chest, coffin”)."},"ipa":["/taː.buːt/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3774","headword_ar":"تَابُوتٌ","root":"tbw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twb","text_ar":"توب"},{"kind":"text","text":". Accord. to some, it belongs to the present art., and was originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwapN","text_ar":"تَابُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4174","headword_ar":"تَابُوتٌ","root":"twb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawabuwtN","text_ar":"تَوَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"not being the characteristic of the fem. gender, (Z, MF, TA,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaluwtN","text_ar":"فَعَلُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"box,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awobu","text_ar":"التَّوْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because what is taken out from it continually returns to it: (AAF, IJ, Z, MF, TA:) or originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwapN","text_ar":"تَابُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K; [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^obuwapN","text_ar":"تَاْبُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being made quiescent, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) [in Chald."},{"kind":"text","text":"?"},{"kind":"text","text":": in Hebr."},{"kind":"text","text":"?"},{"kind":"text","text":":] it signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ribs, with what they contain, as the heart and the liver &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to a chest, or box; (IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbt","text_ar":"تبت"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chest, breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bosom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in that art.:) or [primarily] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ribs, with what they contain, as the heart &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [hence] applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"box:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Towsheeh, MF, TA:) also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabuwtN","text_ar":"تَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbt","text_ar":"تبت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [It is generally applied in the present day to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bier: a coffin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong case that is placed over a grave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaAbiytu","text_ar":"تَوَابِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] El-Kásim Ibn-Maan says that it is the only word in the Kur-án in respect of which the dialects of Kureysh and the Ansár differ; the former pronouncing it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwtN","text_ar":"تَابُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwhN","text_ar":"تَابُوهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) But IB denies that its last letter is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", the fem. termination; asserting the final"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be a radical letter, the measure of the word to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEuwlN","text_ar":"فَاعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its proper place in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbt","text_ar":"تبت"},{"kind":"text","text":": he says that the final"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed in a case of pause, but not generally, into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAt","text_ar":"الفُرَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the Euphrates], in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not the fem. termination. (L, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^awodaEotu taAbuwtiY $ayoy^FA faqadotuhu","text_ar":"مَا اَوْدَعْتُ تَابُوتِى شَيْيًا فَقَدْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not deposited in my bosom anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"of knowledge, or science,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that I have lost."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbt","text_ar":"تبت"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Z","MF","TA","AAF","IJ","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}